						               													<description>Win the maximum number of points by counting how many windows there are in each fa&amp;ccedil;ade and placing the corresponding roof card on the top.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player starts with 6 card on hand and takes turns to play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players can do either of these two actions:&amp;#10;A: Place cards on the table&amp;#10;In each turn, players can place one fa&amp;ccedil;ade card on the table:&amp;#10;- a door card: to start constructing a new building next to the existing ones&amp;#10;- a storey card: placed on top of a building already in construction&amp;#10;In addition to playing your fa&amp;ccedil;ade cards, you can, at any time during your turn, place one or more roof cards on top of the buildings. To do so, the value on your roof card must equal the total number of windows on the building&amp;rsquo;s fa&amp;ccedil;ade.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;B: Swap cards with other players&amp;#10;player can force an exchange with another player if they have 3 grey fa&amp;ccedil;ade cards&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When there are no more cards left in the pile and no more moves possible, the game is over.&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#168;Add up the values of all the roof cards that each player has placed on their buildings. The player with the most points is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
